question:
District category contains Gated Community, Courthouse District, and Arts District.
Supermarkets category contains Eataly, 99 Cents Only Stores, and Bristol Farms.
The number of each Courthouse District 's Eataly equals the difference of each Courthouse District 's 99 Cents Only Stores and each Arts District 's Bristol Farms.
The number of each Gated Community 's Bristol Farms equals each Courthouse District 's Eataly.
The number of each Arts District 's Eataly equals 21.
The number of each Courthouse District 's 99 Cents Only Stores equals each Arts District 's Bristol Farms.
The number of each Arts District 's Bristol Farms equals 1 more than each Arts District 's Eataly.
The number of each Courthouse District 's Bristol Farms equals each Arts District 's Bristol Farms.
How many Bristol Farms does Gated Community have?
solution:
Define each Arts District 's Eataly as q; So q = 21.
Define each Arts District 's Bristol Farms as Z; So Z = 1 + q = 1 + 21 = 22.
Define each Courthouse District 's 99 Cents Only Stores as t; So t = Z = 22.
Define each Courthouse District 's Eataly as n; So n = t - Z = 22 - 22 = 0.
Define each Gated Community 's Bristol Farms as J; So J = n = 0.
